<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFE46839459A344DBF1BFE09" pageId="17" pageNumber="300" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFE46839459A344DBF1BFE09" blockId="17.[151,1436,289,388]" pageId="17" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE46839459A344DBB40FEED" bold="true" box="[199,315,326,352]" pageId="17" pageNumber="300">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from only seven localities in the Kimberley Region of WA (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE4683945C23461BB1EFE09" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[159,357,362,388]" pageId="17" pageNumber="300" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref14689" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2010) Descriptions of 2 new genera and 13 new species of caddisflies from Australia (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 2415 (1), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2415.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Cartwright, 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Here 
<specimenCount id="9D58EAA5FFE4683944E83461B861FE09" box="[437,538,362,388]" pageId="17" pageNumber="300" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE46839471D3461B941FE09" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2010" box="[576,826,362,388]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Wellsomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jalgoodoo">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE46839471D3461B941FE09" box="[576,826,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="300">Wellsomina jalgoodoo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly recorded from the NT for the first time.
</paragraph>
